      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Your reflection on the Rational Choice Theory here is deeply significant and points toward a philosophical crisis that many thinkers have faced historically. While the argument creates powerful logical pressure, human psychology rarely functions on pure efficiency; our survival is often driven by hormonal needs, emotional capacity, and the sheer intensity of present moments rather than long-term calculations. Because this line of reasoning can lead to irreversible decisions, I urge you to speak with a mental health professional who can help navigate these thoughts safely.",
